<p><b>Barry Robert Pepper</b> (born April 4, 1970) is a Canadian actor. He is best known for roles such as Jonnie Goodboy Tyler in <a href="/wiki/Battlefield_Earth_(film)" title="Battlefield Earth (film)"><i>Battlefield Earth</i></a>, <a href="/wiki/Michael_Strank" title="Michael Strank">Sergeant Michael Strank</a> in <i><a href="/wiki/Flags_of_Our_Fathers_(film)" title="Flags of Our Fathers (film)">Flags of Our Fathers</a></i>, Private Daniel Jackson in <i><a href="/wiki/Saving_Private_Ryan" title="Saving Private Ryan">Saving Private Ryan</a></i>, <a href="/wiki/Roger_Maris" title="Roger Maris">Roger Maris</a> in <i><a href="/wiki/61*" title="61*">61*</a></i>, and "Lucky" Ned Pepper in <i><a href="/wiki/True_Grit_(2010_film)" title="True Grit (2010 film)">True Grit</a></i>. He has been nominated for three <a href="/wiki/Screen_Actors_Guild_Awards" title="Screen Actors Guild Awards" class="mw-redirect">Screen Actors Guild Awards</a> and a <a href="/wiki/Golden_Globe_Award" title="Golden Globe Award">Golden Globe Award</a>. In 2011, for his role as <a href="/wiki/Robert_F._Kennedy" title="Robert F. Kennedy">Robert F. Kennedy</a> in the miniseries <i><a href="/wiki/The_Kennedys_(miniseries)" title="The Kennedys (miniseries)">The Kennedys</a></i>, Pepper won the <a href="/wiki/Primetime_Emmy_Award" title="Primetime Emmy Award">Emmy Award</a> for <a href="/wiki/Primetime_Emmy_Award_for_Outstanding_Lead_Actor_in_a_Miniseries_or_a_Movie" title="Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Miniseries or a Movie">Outstanding Lead Actor in a Miniseries or a Movie</a>.</p>
<p></p>
